cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques (Word2Vec) to generate embeddings for IoT devices and analyze their activity footprints. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to identify similar devices, which makes cs.IR a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to generate embeddings, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Since the paper deals with IoT devices, cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with identifying patterns in IoT device activity logs, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible sub-category.
